  "prompt": "How do parents feel when their kid has depression?",
  "response": "Parents often experience a complex mix of emotions when their child is dealing with depression:\n\n1. Worry and Anxiety\n- Deep concern for their child's well-being\n- Fear about potential long-term impacts\n- Constant worry about their child's safety\n\n2. Guilt\n- Questioning their parenting\n- Wondering if they could have prevented the depression\n- Feeling responsible for their child's mental health\n\n3. Helplessness\n- Feeling unable to \"fix\" the problem\n- Struggling to understand what their child is experiencing\n- Wanting to help but not knowing how\n\n4. Sadness\n- Seeing their child suffer\n- Mourning the loss of their child's previous happiness\n- Feeling emotional pain alongside their child\n\n5. Frustration\n- Dealing with mood changes\n- Feeling powerless in supporting their child\n- Navigating treatment and potential resistance\n\n6. Love and Compassion\n- Wanting to support and comfort their child\n- Committed to helping them through the difficult time\n- Unconditional love and support\n\n7. Stress\n- Managing treatment\n- Potential financial strain\n- Emotional exhaustion\n\nThese feelings can vary depending on the individual family, the severity of depression, and their support systems.",
